config ZMK_AGENT_IOS_POINTER_NUDGE
	bool "Send a no-op mouse report on reconnect to wake iOS pointer routing"
	depends on ZMK_BLE && ZMK_POINTING
	default y
	help
	  iOS classifies BLE HID composite keyboard+mouse devices and tends
	  to put AssistiveTouch's pointer routing to sleep across disconnects,
	  forcing the user to toggle AssistiveTouch off and on for scroll to
	  start working again on reconnect.

	  When enabled, this option installs a Bluetooth security_changed
	  callback that emits a tiny net-zero mouse-movement report shortly
	  after each pairing / reconnect reaches encrypted state. macOS and
	  Windows hosts are unaffected (the cursor moves 1px and back in
	  one frame, imperceptibly). On iOS, it appears to wake AssistiveTouch
	  pointer recognition without the manual toggle.

config ZMK_AGENT_IOS_POINTER_NUDGE_DELAY_MS
	int "Delay after security_changed before sending nudge (ms)"
	depends on ZMK_AGENT_IOS_POINTER_NUDGE
	default 1200
	help
	  Time to wait between the BLE link reaching encrypted state and
	  emitting the nudge. iOS subscribes to the HID-input notification
	  CCC after encryption is up; if the nudge fires before that
	  subscription, the report is dropped. ~1s is comfortably past
	  iOS's CCC-write window in practice.
